size=1> For the few couple of years Brenton attended her weapons lessons of and on.  He let Vanthalorn to teach but always watched carefully.  It frightened him to think that his pupil’s latent could have been thrown away by such a careless encounter.  She had to learn to defend herself in a style that suited her, not the larger paladin.  The girl was advancing nicely now that they found a weapon style to suit her.  Her small frame and dancer’s ability made her a wonderful fighter and a joy to watch.<br>
<br>
He wondered what direction to take with her training next.  Her music was far beyond what he had expected already and her weapons skills were almost honed to a level that matched his own.  But she needed to learn hand-to-hand fighting since switching from weapons to instruments was not always a choice a bard had.  But all the monks that he had met were as notorious for attracting a ladies eye as most bards.  <br>
<br>
He didn’t want her distracted a broken heart at this point in her training.  It was time to ask the Lady for help.<br>
<br>
Brenton rose from the bench and went into the temple.  He sought out a young attractive woman that had joined the temple when she was just a few years older than the girl and he had talked to her once about her reasons for joining.  He found her in the gardens staring at a rose bud, “Sister Xanthala may I have a moment of your time.”  <br>
<br>
She rose gracefully and smiled at him, “I knew you would be here soon.  I had a dream about you.”  Walking over she embraced him warmly and he felt a rush of desire at her touch.  This was the reason he wanted her to teach his pupil.  She had a fire of passion for life and love that he had not found matched anywhere.  <br>
<br>
He took her hand in his and kissed the palm gently, they had shared a few nights together and if any woman had ever tempted him to settle down, it was she, “It is time that our fledgling learns the ways of love.”<br>
<br>
Xanthala’s face turned serious, “Are you sure you want me talking to her?  You know I have a much different view on love than the most of the world.”<br>
<br>
“She is a young and beautiful woman who will be meeting a lot of men in her travels.  She needs to know the entire truth of love and passion.” He paused for a moment before continuing, “Too many women learn of love the wrong way.  Men who will use her are in abundance in this world.  I would rather she learns that the Lady’s gift is a two edged blade.”<br>
<br>
“As you wish Brenton.” She sighed softly, then turned to look in his eyes, “but maybe you have a lesson for me first.&quot;  <br>
<br>
He smiled and they walked off towards her rooms.<br>
